# ============================================================
# QUICK START GUIDE - Environment Configuration
# ============================================================
#
# This file explains how to set up your .env file
#
# ============================================================

# STEP 1: Copy the example file
# ============================================================
# cp .env.example .env


# STEP 2: Edit the .env file with your credentials
# ============================================================
# nano .env  (or use your preferred editor)


# STEP 3: Update these REQUIRED values in .env:
# ============================================================

# DATABASE_URL - Your MySQL connection string
# Format: mysql+pymysql://username:password@host:port/database
# Example: mysql+pymysql://root:Welcome%40123@localhost:3306/pms_dev_nmg_90
# Note: Special characters in password must be URL-encoded:
#   @ → %40
#   # → %23
#   ! → %21

# OPENAI_API_KEY - Your OpenAI API key
# Get it from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Format: sk-proj-...

# SECRET_KEY - Secret key for JWT tokens
# Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
# Or: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"


# STEP 4: Test your configuration
# ============================================================
# python test_env_config.py


# STEP 5: Start the application
# ============================================================
# uvicorn backend.main:app --reload


# ============================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================================

# Error: "Field required" for DATABASE_URL
# → Make sure .env file exists and contains DATABASE_URL=...

# Error: "Database connection failed"
# → Check your database credentials
# → Verify MySQL is running
# → Check if password has special characters (URL-encode them)

# Error: "OpenAI API key not configured"
# → Verify OPENAI_API_KEY is set in .env
# → Check for extra spaces or quotes

# ============================================================
# SECURITY REMINDERS
# ============================================================

# ✅ DO:
# - Keep .env file private
# - Use different credentials for dev/staging/production
# - Generate strong random keys
# - Add .env to .gitignore (already done)

# ❌ DON'T:
# - Commit .env to version control
# - Share credentials in chat/email
# - Use production credentials in development

